"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-team-gb-medal-prediction-paris-b1172347.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  Great Britainare tipped to finish theParis Olympicsin fourth place in themedalstable.  Gracenote, which predicts the medal tally and final positions for each Games, is forecasting a total of 63 medals forTeam GB.  In its model, that would put the British with the third-highest medal count behind the United States and China, but pushed into fourth by hosts France by virtue of their higher predicted gold medal tally (27 to 17).  The anticipated haul is largely similar to the last Games in Tokyo, whereTeam GB ended fourth in the tablewith 64 medals, 22 of which were gold.  In its report, Gracenote wrote: \\\"Great Britain can sustain its winning performance of 60 or more medals for a fourth successive Games.  \\\"British success over the past three summer Olympics has been built on having medal winners in at least 20 sports.  \\\"Gracenote's final virtual medal table has winners in 21 different sports, suggesting this trend is set to continue.  \\\"Prior to the 2012 Olympics, Great Britain had not won medals in at least 20 sports for over 100 years, since hosting [the Games] in 1908.\\\"  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disrupt